{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Executive Summary\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 VibeSwap is the first fair-launch omnichain DEX that eliminates MEV through commit-reveal batch auctions with uniform clearing prices. We are live on Base mainnet. Our AI co-founder JARVIS runs the community autonomously. We are building the infrastructure for Cooperative Capitalism \u8212- where self-interest serves the collective.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This document outlines our marketing strategy: positioning, target audiences, channels, messaging, and execution timeline.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 1. Positioning\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.1 The Problem\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Every major DEX today has the same fundamental flaw: {\b the order in which trades execute determines who profits.} Miners, validators, and MEV bots extract value by front-running, sandwiching, and reordering transactions. Users subsidize this extraction with every swap.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The numbers are staggering:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Over $1.4 billion extracted via MEV on Ethereum alone (2020-2025)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Average retail trader loses 0.5-2% per trade to sandwich attacks\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Front-running bots consistently outbid real users for execution priority\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is not a feature of decentralization. It is a failure of mechanism design.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 1.2 Our Solution\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 VibeSwap eliminates MEV through 10-second batch auctions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Commit Phase (8s)}: Users submit encrypted order hashes with deposits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Reveal Phase (2s)}: Orders are revealed with optional priority bids\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Settlement}: Orders are shuffled using cryptographic randomness (Fisher-Yates with XORed secrets) and executed at a single uniform clearing price\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 No one can front-run because orders are encrypted during submission. No one can sandwich because all trades in a batch execute at the same price. Priority bids pay for urgency without affecting the clearing price for others.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b One-liner: Trade without getting robbed. Build without getting diluted.}\par}
