{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 2. Target Audiences\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.1 Primary: Degens Who Hate Front-Running\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Who they are}: Active on-chain traders (10+ trades/week) who have been sandwiched, front-run, or otherwise MEV-extracted. They\u8217're crypto-native, technically literate, and vocally frustrated with current DEX infrastructure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Where they are}: Crypto Twitter, Discord trading servers, DeFi Llama leaderboards, on-chain analytics dashboards.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b What they want}: A DEX that doesn\u8217't steal from them. They will trade more volume on a fair platform because they keep more of their returns.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Message}: \u8220"Every trade on Uniswap, someone is front-running you. On VibeSwap, trades are encrypted and batch-settled. Same price for everyone. Zero MEV.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.2 Secondary: Builders Who Want Fair Launches\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Who they are}: Protocol founders, token creators, and project teams who want to launch tokens without VC extraction, insider trading, or sniping bots.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Where they are}: GitHub, Ethereum research forums, hackathons, builder communities (Buildspace, ETHGlobal alumni).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b What they want}: A launch platform where early buyers don\u8217't get exploited by bots, and the team doesn\u8217't have to give away 20% to VCs for \u8220"distribution.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Message}: \u8220"Launch on VibeSwap. No sniping bots. No front-running. Your community gets the same price as everyone else. Fair launch means fair launch.\u8221"\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 2.3 Tertiary: Communities Tired of Extractive Platforms\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Who they are}: DAO members, governance participants, and crypto idealists who believe DeFi should serve users, not rent-seekers.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Where they are}: Governance forums, DAO tooling communities, crypto podcasts focused on governance and mechanism design.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b What they want}: Proof that Cooperative Capitalism works. A protocol that distributes value to contributors, not extractors.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Message}: \u8220"VibeSwap\u8217's fees go to liquidity providers and governance stakers via Shapley distribution \u8212- mathematically proportional to marginal contribution. No pre-mine. No VC cut. The protocol rewards the people who build it.\u8221"\par}
